              <div class="text-neutral-600">Any emotion (sadness, boredom, joy)</div>
            </div>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-3 p-4 bg-neutral-50">
              <div class="font-medium text-neutral-800">Timing</div>
              <div class="text-neutral-600">During or right after stress</div>
              <div class="text-neutral-600">Anytime emotions arise</div>
            </div>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-3 p-4">
              <div class="font-medium text-neutral-800">Duration</div>
              <div class="text-neutral-600">Often temporary, situational</div>
              <div class="text-neutral-600">Can be chronic, habitual</div>
            </div>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-3 p-4 bg-neutral-50">
              <div class="font-medium text-neutral-800">Root Cause</div>
              <div class="text-neutral-600">Physiological (cortisol)</div>
              <div class="text-neutral-600">Psychological (coping)</div>
            </div>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-3 p-4">
              <div class="font-medium text-neutral-800">Foods Craved</div>
              <div class="text-neutral-600">High-energy comfort foods</div>
              <div class="text-neutral-600">Varies by emotion</div>
            </div>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-3 p-4 bg-neutral-50">
              <div class="font-medium text-neutral-800">Awareness</div>
              <div class="text-neutral-600">Often recognized in moment</div>
              <div class="text-neutral-600">May be unconscious</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- How EmotionEat Helps -->
    <section class="py-16 md:py-20 px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 bg-white">
      <div class="container mx-auto max-w-4xl">
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-6">
          How EmotionEat Helps With Both
        </h2>

        <p class="text-lg text-neutral-600 mb-8 leading-relaxed">
          Whether you're dealing with stress eating, emotional eating, or both, EmotionEat provides personalized support:
        </p>

        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div class="flex items-start p-4 bg-primary-50 rounded-xl">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-primary-400 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 mr-4">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-white" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 20l-5.447-2.724A1 1 0 013 16.382V5.618a1 1 0 011.447-.894L9 7m0 13l6-3m-6 3V7m6 10l4.553 2.276A1 1 0 0021 18.382V7.618a1 1 0 00-.553-.894L15 4m0 13V4m0 0L9 7"></path>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-800 mb-1">Trigger mapping</h3>
              <p class="text-neutral-600">Identifies whether stress, emotions, or both drive your eating — giving you clarity on your unique patterns</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start p-4 bg-secondary-50 rounded-xl">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-secondary-400 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 mr-4">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-white" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M8 12h.01M12 12h.01M16 12h.01M21 12c0 4.418-4.03 8-9 8a9.863 9.863 0 01-4.255-.949L3 20l1.395-3.72C3.512 15.042 3 13.574 3 12c0-4.418 4.03-8 9-8s9 3.582 9 8z"></path>
